Properties.Description:
Body condition score (BCS) is an easy-to-use tool that describes the relative fatness of beef cattle. 

A nine-point BCS scale can be used to manage the cow herd.

Percentage of empty body fat corresponding to each body condition score on a scale from 1 to 9.

BCS    Empty Body Fat (%)
1      3.8
2      7.5
3      11.3
4      15.1
5      18.8
6      22.6
7      26.4
8      30.2
9      33.9

The most important characteristics describing the nine-point scale of body condition scoring system:

- emaciated
- very thin
- thin
- borderline
- moderate
- good
- fleshy
- obese
- very obese
